title: Lemlands IF
text:
Lemlands Idrottsförening or Lemlands IF is a <a href="Finland">Finnish</a> sports club situated in <a href="Lemland">Lemland</a> in <a href="%C3%85land">Åland</a>. The club is best known for its <a href="association%20football">football</a> section. Lemlands IF is competing in the <a href="Swedish%20Football%20Division%207">Swedish Football Division 7</a>. <a href="Wilhelm%20Ingves">Wilhelm Ingves</a>, a striker of the <a href="Veikkausliiga">Finnish Premier Division</a> outfit <a href="IFK%20Mariehamn">IFK Mariehamn</a>, is a former youth player of Lemlands IF.
The women's football section of Lemlands IF merged with <a href="IF%20Finstr%C3%B6ms%20Kamraterna">IF Finströms Kamraterna</a> in 2004. New club <a href="%C3%85land%20United">Åland United</a> has been playing in the Finnish top division <a href="Kansallinen%20Liiga">Kansallainen Liiga</a> since 2006. The most notable female footballer of Lemlands IF is <a href="Ing-Marie%20Holmberg">Ing-Marie Holmberg</a>, who represented <a href="Finland%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Finland</a> in 21 internationals during the 1990s.
